 <p class="titulo_2_noticia_azul_oscuro"><strong>Description of  the postdoctoral position </strong><br>
  <strong> teaching and learning writing</strong></p>
<p>The candidate is expected to contribute  with research regarding Writing processes at the Area of 'Language Teaching and  Learning for maximum impact' of the Center for Advanced Research in Education  (CIAE); hence he/she is expected to conduct research in topics relevant to  Teaching and Learning of Writing in primary and secondary schools from a cognitive,  developmental sociocultural, or pedagogical approach. In addition it is  expected that the candidate contributes to &nbsp;teachers' professional development programs  (based on his/her research) and collaborates actively with researchers of the  Area.</p>
<p>
  <strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>PhD degree in Linguistic,  Psychology, Educational Sciences, or a related discipline, obtained not before  2013. Candidates currently in the process of graduation must be in possession  of their degree by March 2018.</li>
  <li>Relevant scientific  publications.</li>
  <li>Strong teamwork and  communication skills.</li>
  <li>Experience with  interdisciplinary cooperation is highly desirable.</li>
  <li>Strong knowledge of Spanish  teaching, grammar and linguistic in Spanish language</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Research  proposal:</strong></p>
<p>The candidate must present a brief research  proposal (max 3,000 words) related to the aforementioned topics. The proposal  must describe the main research questions, problem, aims, methodology,  resources needed for its execution, and its contribution to Education.</p>
